Project Plan: The following activities will be implemented:
- Capacity building and training of farmers on best organic farming practices,  improved maize seed farming and financial literacy training. Training will be done on quarterly basis.
- Contacting and establishing strategic partnership agreements with potential buyers to encourage marketing and distribution of harvested maize crops;
- Enhance provision of micro credit services to the farmers;
- Provide storage facility for farmers to store their maize produce before being sold;
- Increasing awareness on gender roles and the involvement of women in households food security planning and decision making;
- Enhance awareness raising on the project within the Ghanaian migrant community in the Netherlands and other European countries.

Goal Overview: The goals of the project are:
- to provide clean portable water for the community of Botogwina;
- To supply water for irrigation;
- To decrease the workload of women and children fetching water for the households;

Project Plan: The project will consists of the following:
- Training of the management team;
- Recruitment and training of volunteers for the operation and maintenance of the borehole;
- Organization of information meetings for the community;
- Drilling the borehole;
- Construction of the water tank;
- Installation of the electricity system;
- Investigation of the water treatment if needed;

Goal Overview: - Integration of adolescent reproductive health in primary health care;
- Improvement the practice of 700 traditional medicine practitioners and linkage with orthodox health care;
- Improvement of the nutritional status of 1000 children aged 2-5 years;
- Strengthening of the capacity of 300 Traditional Birth Attendants as change agents;
- Enhance the capaticty of ACDEP’s health unit.

Project Plan: The project consists of the following activities:

- Contracting a company for the drilling, construction and mechanization of one borehole;
- Management and monitoring of the building of the water collection point.

Project Plan: In both projects in the villages groups are formed of approximately fifteen persons, male, female or mixed. 

Every two weeks the group comes together with the fieldofficer of the project. The people are then instructed in the application of organic farming and in various other subjects. When sufficient progress has been made the frequency is reduced to once every four weeks and later to once every two months. If after several years the groups have sufficient knowledge to work independently they are weaned off, but remain in contact with the project.

The main activities in the program of SEISUD and ZEFP are:
- Creating consciousness of importance of organic farming and actual teaching and practical application of it;
- Accompany groups in activities such as planting and growing of trees, making compost, teaching crop change, making stone or earth bunds to control erosion, post-harvest loss management;
- Fight fires, including burning of crop residue;
- Planting and growing of trees;

At SEISUD, in 2012 an agricultural training center has been established, the Ghana Institute of Organic Farmers. In 2014 at this school, an electricity system will be realized and the construction of the hostel for female students will be finalized. Both the electricity and the hostel are needed for the school to be recognized by the government.

Goal Overview: We seek to strengthen the National Catholic Health Services. This is undertaken by
-Strengthening human resources for healthcare delivery;
-Building capacity for comprehensive and quality health care that meets patients'expectations.
-Improving HIV/AIDS services, eliminating stigma and discrimination;
-Ensuring accessibility, rational use and quality of medicines;
-Improving financial management and sustainability;
-Improving information management and research
-Improving overall pass rates and the curriculum in the training colleges

Project Plan: In both projects in the villages groups are formed of approximately fifteen persons, male, female or mixed. 

Every two weeks the group comes together with the field-officer of the project. The people are then instructed in the application of organic farming and in various other subjects. When sufficient progress has been made the frequency is reduced to once every four weeks and later to once every two months. If after several years the groups have sufficient knowledge to work independently they are weaned off, but remain in contact with the project.

The main activities in the program of SEISUD and ZEFP are:
- Creating consciousness of importance of organic farming and actual teaching and practical application of it;
- Accompany groups in activities such as planting and growing of trees, making compost, teaching crop change, making stone or earth bunds to control erosion, post-harvest loss management;
- Fight fires, including burning of crop residue;
- Planting and growing of trees;
- Building of a training center for the region and beyond;
- Micro-credit program;
- Strengthen the position of women

Project Plan: The main activities of  this project include:

- Training and supervision of Area Managers;
- Registration of local NGO’s and opening of bank accounts for each Area Manager;
- Identification of  progressive farmers and other entrepreneurs; 
- Evaluation of loan applications and underlying business plans;
- Formulation of loan agreements and repayment schedules;
- Financial administration of Bebobakery accounts and Area Managers accounts.
